<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-24T17:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-24T17:29:00-05:00" n="802" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/600</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The War Trade Board Representative in Cuba</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MHH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-24T17:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.32 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>For Department of State and War Trade Board:</p>
                        <p>No. 8. Steamship <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_A1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Alfonso XIII</hi>
                            </persName> of the Spanish line which arrives here in a few days has
                            engaged to carry to Mexico 26,000 bags of sugar. Have been asked to
                            bunker her, but I disapprove using our coal for this purpose. Am I
                            authorized to refuse? I have declined to bunker all Cuban ships for this
                            purpose.</p>
                        <p>In a confidential conference with the President on March 22 he informed
                            me he was in accord with my actions and expressed a wish that the
                            Spanish boats be treated in the same way.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MHH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>